04784nam a22008295i 9780226639413DE-B159720210621102733.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210621t20192019ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a2018055501  a97802266394137 a10.7208/97802266394132doi  a(DE-B1597)535522  a(OCoLC)1109390887  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL00aBQ5630.V5bP325 2019 4aBF637.M4 7aSOC0000002bisacsh04a158.122231 aPagis, Michal, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aInward :bVipassana Meditation and the Embodiment of the Self /cMichal Pagis. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2019] 4c©2019  a1 online resource (240 p.) :b2 line drawings  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aFieldwork Encounters and Discoveries00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tNote on Terminology -- t1. Turning Inward -- t2. The Popularization of Meditation -- t3. Collective Solitude -- t4. Meditation in Daily Life -- t5. Negotiating Intimate Social Relations -- t6. Becoming a Meditator: Life-Course Orientations -- t7. Bodies, Selves, and the Social World -- tMethodological Appendix: Ethnography of Experience -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWestern society has never been more interested in interiority. Indeed, it seems more and more people are deliberately looking inward—toward the mind, the body, or both. Michal Pagis’s Inward focuses on one increasingly popular channel for the introverted gaze: vipassana meditation, which has spread from Burma to more than forty countries and counting. Lacing her account with vivid anecdotes and personal stories, Pagis turns our attention not only to the practice of vipassana but to the communities that have sprung up around it. Inward is also a social history of the westward diffusion of Eastern religious practices spurred on by the lingering effects of the British colonial presence in India. At the same time Pagis asks knotty questions about what happens when we continually turn inward, as she investigates the complex relations between physical selves, emotional selves, and our larger social worlds. Her book sheds new light on evergreen topics such as globalization, social psychology, and the place of the human body in the enduring process of self-awareness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aMeditationxBuddhismxSocial aspects. 0aMeditationxSocial aspects. 0aMeditation. 0aMind and body. 0aSelf. 0aVipaśyanā (Buddhism) 0aVipaśyanā (Buddhism). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aBuddhist.  aattention.  aawareness.  abody.  adiffusion.  aexperience.  ainteraction.  ainteriority.  ameditation.  amindfulness.  aself.  asolitude.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226639413423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226639413.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DSWb2019